snippet.textDisplay: 6:34 A R Rahman's smile says it all ! It's very peculiar of Rahman to transform the song with certain elements. Well in this song, it starts from 3:44, the song goes to a warp drive. The percussions followed by another instrument at 3:49 (which I don't know, pls help me with the name 😉 ), and then the Continuum Keyboard by Rahman himself, followed by Mohini Dey's Bass, and well, the moment you think you're settling down for a spiritual experience again, Farah's infectious smile (I copied this, because there was no better word) gives you a happy high. And that goes on, you don't want the song to end, but 7:05 ends like less than a moment. Einstein's theory of relativity is so true here 😉
